\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S24}{\ignorespaces The results of our second extrapolation, including a) the mean age of abandonment, and b) the total area abandoned into the future. Colors corresponding to each site are consistent across the three panels. These extrapolation assume recultivation based on the mean decay trend for each site Figure 3 and annual new abandonment based on the mean annual gain in abandonment shown in Figure \ref {fig:turnover-grid} (dark green bars).\relax }}{37}{figure.caption.32}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {S25}{\ignorespaces Extrapolating area by age bin, assuming a 1) each site follows the mean recultivation (``decay'') rate, and 2) a constant area abandoned each year until 2017 (based on the mean annual area abandoned at each site), followed by a linearly declining area abandoned each year until reaching 0 in 2050.\relax }}{38}{figure.caption.33}%
